</li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGazette28950" class="citation magazine cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.thegazette.co.uk/London/issue/28950/page/8603">"No. 28950"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_London_Gazette" title="The London Gazette">The London Gazette</a></i>. 23 October 1914. p.&#160;8603.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+London+Gazette&amp;rft.atitle=No.+28950&amp;rft.pages=8603&amp;rft.date=1914-10-23&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thegazette.co.uk%2FLondon%2Fissue%2F28950%2Fpage%2F8603&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARichard+Hutton+Davies" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Inglefield, pp. 3–4, gives it as "within a few weeks" of formation. Note that some sources, such as a note in the personnel file, give him as taking command of the division in April 1915.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Clayton.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Letter of 1 February 1965, Maj. E. E. Andrews; in personnel file</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Inglefield, pp. 7, 15–23, &amp; 44. Clayton refers to him being sent to England in "late 1916", which appears to be an error.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://nzetc.victoria.ac.nz/tm/scholarly/tei-WH1-NZRi-t1-back-d3.html">Appendix III</a>, <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAustin1924" class="citation book cs1">Austin, Lt. Col. W. S. (1924). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://nzetc.victoria.ac.nz/tm/scholarly/tei-WH1-NZRi.html"><i>The official history of the New Zealand Rifle Brigade</i></a>. Wellington: L. T. Watkins.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+official+history+of+the+New+Zealand+Rifle+Brigade&amp;rft.place=Wellington&amp;rft.pub=L.+T.+Watkins&amp;rft.date=1924&amp;rft.aulast=Austin&amp;rft.aufirst=Lt.+Col.+W.+S.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnzetc.victoria.ac.nz%2Ftm%2Fscholarly%2Ftei-WH1-NZRi.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARichard+Hutton+Davies" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.wanlessweb.org/TNG/showmedia.php?mediaID=286&amp;medialinkID=340">Obituary of General O'Gowan</a>, <i>The Times</i>, 17 December 1947. Appendix III of Austin confirms that O'Gowan directly succeeded Davies.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Bourne; see also Biographical Note by Maj. E. E. Andrews in personnel file. Address drawn from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.1914-1918.net/hospitals_uk.htm">The Military Hospitals of Great Britain</a> and <i>London Gazette</i> death notice.</span>
</li>
